# INObjectResolutionResult

**Class**

A resolution result for an Object associated with an intent.

## Declaration

```swift
class INObjectResolutionResult
```

## Overview

An [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INObjectResolutionResult] object is what you return when resolving Object related parameters of an intent object. Use the creation method that best reflects your ability to successfully resolve the parameter.

For additional resolution options, see [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INIntentResolutionResult].

## Creating a Resolution Result Object

- **success(with:)**: Creates an object whose resolution involves the successful matching of the specified parameter.
- **confirmationRequired(with:)**: Creates an object whose resolution requires that the user must confirm the value before proceeding.
- **disambiguation(with:)**: Creates an object whose resolution requires the user to select from among the specified objects.

## Custom Resolution Results

- **INEnumResolutionResult**: A resolution result for an enumeration associated with an intent.

## Inherits From

- INIntentResolutionResult

## Conforms To

- CVarArg
- CustomDebugStringConvertible
- CustomStringConvertible
- Equatable
- Hashable
- NSObjectProtocol
